If you cannot build a genuine community, you can not support a project long-term. Community requires both trust and true engagement. Foster those and you will make it.

2) Stop putting Hype before true Community. This is making it all a numbers game and not always an honest one. Sell out in seconds? That was a bot, not your community. 50k followers and no sell-out. That was a different bot.

1) Stop with the blind trust. This goes for collectors and teams. Don't just superficially DYOR. Dive as deep as you can before buying. Ask questions. Devs and founders need to ask artists questions about how they work. Artists need to set compensation expectations early.
